abstract_problem: This is a set cover problem.we have N sets,The goal is to select the minimum number of sets such that each integer i from 1 to I is covered a number once. The sets available for selection are stored in sets S1 , and each set lists the integers it covers. Sets in S1 can only be selected 0 or 1 times.

files_1.description: Each row in Table S1 represents a set. These sets can only be selected 0 or 1 times. If a set contains a certain integer, the corresponding column in Table S1 is 1; otherwise, it is 0.
